    think='I\'ve found several issues already. Let me continue reading the Flutt
er files and other critical components.\n\nKey findings so far:\n1. **Blocking**
: Migration uses `AUTO_INCREMENT` for `sequence_id` - db.md explicitly forbids n
on-primary key AUTO_INCREMENT. It says "除主键外，禁止为其他列使用 AUTO_INCREMEN
T". The `sequence_id` should use an app-layer generator like Snowflake or UUID v
7 timestamp.\n2. The entity also uses `@Generated("increment")` for `sequence_id
` - same issue.\n3. The `send-message.dto.ts` has `content` as optional (`@IsOpt
ional()`) but the service checks `dto.type === "text" && (!dto.content || dto.co
ntent.length > 500)`. However, looking at the PR body, there was a fix: "fix: re
solve #64 - make SendMessageDto.content optional for image messages". This is ac
tually the current state after fixes.\n4. The DTO uses `@IsMessageContent()` cus
tom validator. I need to check what that does.\n5. `getConversations` uses nativ
e SQL with `?` placeholders - that\'s good per db.md.\n6. The gateway emits even
ts after service calls return. But `sendMessage` already commits the transaction
. The gateway then emits `message:receive`, `message:delivered`, `conversation:u
pdated`. This is fine.\n\nWait, let me check the message-content.validator.ts to
understand the DTO validation.',
    encrypted=None
)
