!== "string"` - but when `content` is undefined, `typeof value` is `"undefined"`
, so it returns `false`. This means the validator REQUIRES content to be a strin
g even when optional!\n\nWait, let me re-read the validator:\n```typescript\nval
idate(value: unknown, args: ValidationArguments) {\n  if (typeof value !== "stri
ng") {\n    return false;\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nWhen `content` is undefined (im
age message without text), `typeof value` is `"undefined"`, so `return false`. T
his means `@IsMessageContent()` combined with `@IsOptional()` still fails becaus
e `@IsOptional()` only skips validation when the property is `null` or `undefine
d`, but custom decorators registered with `registerDecorator` may not be skipped
by `@IsOptional()` automatically...\n\nActually, looking at `class-validator` do
cs, `@IsOptional()` does skip validation for custom decorators when the value is
`null` or `undefined`. Wait, let me verify this. Actually, `@IsOptional()` uses 
`validateIf` internally - it checks if value is null/undefined and skips. So if 
`content` is undefined, `@IsOptional()` should skip `@IsMessageContent()`.\n\nHm
m, but the PR description mentions "fix: resolve #64 - make SendMessageDto.conte
nt optional for image messages". This suggests there WAS a bug where `content` w
as required. Looking at the fix commit, it made `content` optional. But wait, th
e current `SendMessageDto` has `content?: string` with `@IsOptional()`. That see
ms correct now.\n\nBut wait - the validator still requires `typeof value !== "st
ring"` to return false. If `@IsOptional()` is used, class-validator should skip 
the `IsMessageContent` validator when the value is undefined. So this should be 
fine.\n\nHowever, let me check if there are any remaining issues. The DTO has:\n
```typescript\n@IsOptional()\n@IsMessageContent()\ncontent?: string;\n```\n\nAnd
the validator:\n```typescript\nvalidate(value: unknown, args: ValidationArgument
s) {\n  if (typeof value !== "string") {\n    return false;\n  }\n  const type =
(args.object as Record<string, unknown>).type;\n  if (type === "text" && value.l
ength > 500) {\n    return false;\n  }\n  return true;\n}\n```\n\nWait - if `con
tent` is provided but is an empty string `""` for an image message, `typeof valu
