ntity uses `@Generated("increment")`. This is explicitly forbidden by `db.md` li
ne 46: "除主键外，禁止为其他列使用 AUTO_INCREMENT（包括 TypeORM 的 `@Generated("
increment")`）". The PRD also says `sequence_id` should be `bigserial` (which in
MySQL context was meant to be auto-increment, but the project db.md overrides th
is with the app-layer generator rule). However, looking at the PRD again: "seque
nce_id 使用数据库自增 bigserial". And db.md says "若业务需要单调递增序列号（如消
息排序 sequence_id），应改用应用层发号器（如雪花算法、UUID v7 的时间戳部分），而
非数据库自增". These two conflict. But the project standard (db.md) is more spec
ific and says it\'s forbidden. This is a clear violation.\n\nWait, actually the 
PRD was written before db.md was updated. The db.md is the current enforced stan
dard. The migration and entity violate db.md. This is Blocking because it affect
s database schema and future migration to sharding.\n\n2. **Blocking/Major**: Th
e PR checklist says `make test` is NOT checked. The TEMPLATE-fullstack-feature.m
d says `make test` is part of the delivery checklist. The PR description shows `
- [ ] make test[...truncated]`. This means tests were not fully run. However, th
is alone might not be blocking if the tests actually pass. But the developer did
n\'t confirm it. Per the template, this is required.\n\nActually, let me re-read
the PR body: "- [ ] `make test`[...truncated]". It was truncated but seems unche
cked. However, looking at the PR commits: there were fix commits "fix: 修复 PR #
64 review 问题" and "fix: resolve #64 - make SendMessageDto.content optional for
image messages". This suggests the PR has already gone through some review/fix c
ycles.\n\nBut wait - I\'m the review agent for PR #64. The PR body from `gh pr v
iew` might be the original description, and the fix commits might have been adde
d after. The current branch state is what I need to review.\n\nLet me check if `
make test` is actually passing by running it. Actually, I might not have the ful
l environment set up. But I can check if the backend tests at least compile/run.
\n\n3. **Major**: `SwChatInputBar` lacks auto-select on focus. Per flutter.md: "
获得焦点时自动全选旧内容 - Maestro inputText 在 Flutter TextField 上的行为是追加
而非替换。若旧内容未被清除，新输入会与旧值拼接成无效内容。必须在获得焦点时自动全
选". The Maestro flow does `tapOn: id: "chat_input_field"` then `inputText: "Hel
lo E2E"`. Without auto-select, if there\'s any existing text, it would append. T
his is a Major issue for E2E compatibility.\n\n4. **Major**: The `message-conten
t.validator.ts` custom validator checks `typeof value !== "string"` and returns 
false. When combined with `@IsOptional()`, class-validator should skip it when u
ndefined. BUT there\'s a potential issue: if `content` is provided as `null` (no
t undefined), `@IsOptional()` might not skip it, and the validator would fail. H
owever, this is a minor edge case.\n\nActually, looking more carefully: the `@Is
MessageContent()` doesn\'t check if the value is empty for text messages. The DT
O allows `content: ""` for text messages, but the service rejects it. This is th
e DTO-Service inconsistency mentioned in nestjs.md. But this is more of a Minor 
issue.\n\n5. **Minor**: The `im.service.ts` `getConversations` method fetches un
read counts from Redis in a serial loop (`for...of` with `await`). With up to 20
conversations, this makes 20 sequential Redis round-trips. This could be optimiz
ed with `mget` or pipelining. But for MVP with 20 items, it\'s probably acceptab
le.\n\n6. **Minor**: The `ImBloc` uses `dioClient` directly to build the socket 
URL. It does `baseUrl.replaceFirst(RegExp(r\'/api/v1/?$\'), \'\')`. This is a bi
t fragile but acceptable.\n\n7. **Minor**: The `chat_page.dart` `_scrollToBottom
` scrolls to `0` which is correct for a reversed ListView.\n\n8. The `app.dart` 
correctly registers `ImBloc` at the App level and connects/disconnects based on 
auth state. Good.\n\n9. The `ImBloc` correctly handles cross-session message buf
fering via `_pendingMessages`. Good.\n\n10. The `ImBloc` emits `MessageSending` 
then emits `MessagesLoaded` if socket is disconnected. This follows the pattern 
in flutter.md for handling offline state.\n\n11. **Minor**: The `message.entity.
ts` uses `@Column("bigint")` with `@Generated("increment")`. In MySQL, `AUTO_INC
REMENT` requires the column to be indexed. The migration adds `INDEX idx_message
s_sequence_id (sequence_id)` so that requirement is met. But the db.md rule is s
till violated.\n\nWait, I need to reconsider the `AUTO_INCREMENT` issue. The PRD
explicitly says `sequence_id 使用数据库自增 bigserial`. And db.md says:\n> 若业
务需要单调递增序列号（如消息排序 sequence_id），应改用应用层发号器（如雪花算法、
UUID v7 的时间戳部分），而非数据库自增\n\nThese are in direct conflict. The PRD 
says use database auto-increment, db.md says use app-layer generator. Which one 
takes precedence?\n\nIn the review framework, I should base my judgment on proje
ct documents. The db.md is listed as a "编码规范文档" and is the current standar
d. The PRD is a product requirement. When technical standards conflict with PRD,
the technical standard usually takes precedence for implementation details, espe
cially when the standard explicitly calls out the exact scenario ("如消息排序 se
quence_id").\n\nHowever, I should note this as a Major or Blocking issue dependi
ng on how strictly it\'s enforced. The db.md says "禁止" (forbidden), which is v
ery strong. And it mentions "Agent 修改 Entity 后，必须同时生成并提交 Migration 
文件" but also says "禁止为其他列使用 AUTO_INCREMENT". This is a hard rule.\n\nL
et me check if there are any other issues I missed.\n\n12. **Minor**: The `docs/
